to compile:

export SYSROOT=~/powkiddy/sysroot
export CC=arm-gcc
export CXX=arm-buildroot-linux-uclibcgnueabi-g++
export AR=arm-buildroot-linux-uclibcgnueabi-ar
export LD=arm-buildroot-linux-uclibcgnueabi-ld
export RANLIB=arm-buildroot-linux-uclibcgnueabi-ranlib
export STRIP=arm-buildroot-linux-uclibcgnueabi-strip
export PATH=~/powkiddy/buildroot-2015.02/output/host/usr/bin:$PATH

To connect to the console, you must have the USB-C (charger) connected and USB-A cable ton USB1 port.
Switch ON the console (press 3s the poweron button) until you see on the display an image with computer and console! if you are on ADB shell on charging screen, the framebuffer and the buttons are not working correctly!

mount the sdcard : mount /dev/mmcblk0p1 /mnt/card/

to run in adb shell:
/etc/backlight.sh open
export HOME=/mnt/card/
export SDL_VIDEODRIVER=fbcon
export SDL_NOMOUSE=1
export SDL_MOUSEDEV=/dev/null
export SDL_VIDEO_FBCON_ROTATION=CCW
echo "0,0" > /sys/class/graphics/fb0/pan


sdl1.2:
SDL1.2 has been modified to match the framebuffer resolution of the X39 pro (854x480) in src/video/fbcon/SDL_fbvideo.c

configure : see _compile in SDL folder :  ./configure \
    --host=arm-buildroot-linux-uclibcgnueabi \
    --prefix=$SYSROOT/usr \
    --disable-video-opengl \
    --disable-video-x11 \
    --disable-video-wayland \
    --enable-video-fbcon \
    --disable-haptic \
    --disable-joystick-hidapi \
    --enable-joystick \
    --enable-audio \
    --disable-tests \
    CC=$CC \
    CXX=$CXX \
    AR=$AR \
    LD=$LD \
    RANLIB=$RANLIB \
    STRIP=$STRIP \
    CFLAGS="--sysroot=$SYSROOT" \
    LDFLAGS="--sysroot=$SYSROOT"
then make and make install

gnuboy:
configure : see _configure in gnuboy folder :  ./configure  --host=arm-buildroot-linux-uclibcgnueabi     --prefix=/tmp/gnuboy-install     --with-sdl     --without-sdl2 --with-sound=no --with-fb --without-x --disable-sdltest
then make

copy from etc/powkiddy.rc config file
adb push etc/powkiddy.rc /mnt/card/gnuboy.rc

push the binary
adb push sdlgnuboy /mnt/card

and SDL1.2
adb push sysroot/usr/lib/libSDL-1.2.so.0 /mnt/card

copy a rom on /mnt/card
run the exports listed above then ./sdlgnuboy& and it should work :-)
ps: i've added a lot of logs for troubleshooting and it require you to press a button to start really the emulator...


